Similar allegations have now emerged at Leopards with senior players said to be at the center of the vice.A senior player said to have been very close to Kimani tried to influence few other players to stage a protest against Kimani’s departure after the hiring of Patrick Aussems. AFC Leopards managment has blamed senior players after the team boycotted training on Tuesday demanding to be paid their salaries. 

Contacted, the club treasurer Maurice Chichi confirmed the office had not paid the January salaries only and not two months, adding that they were processing the payments when they learned of unrest in the team. 



